Latorre T wrote a review Oct 2022
Boston10 contributions4 helpful votes
A nice place to stay
Stayed here for 8 nights in September. Very clean and friendly. The pool in the middle of the hotel was perfect. The room was plenty big enough and the shower had enough pressure. The ac worked well which was much appreciated. And the location was perfect. Close to the beach but not in the middle of everything. Would definitely go back.
Date of stay: September 2022
Ellen wrote a review Apr 2021
Hanoi, Vietnam3 contributions2 helpful votes
Lovely place
Our last night was in Da Nang. Hotel in a quiet alley, good location very close to the beach. The staff are so friendly (Anh Tai), helpful, polite and very cute! The rooms are really clean and look beautiful with plenty of space. Overall an amazing hotel with value for money. MotorBike rental is perfect with very safe, good quality bikes.
Date of stay: April 2021
djarch and Anne wrote a review Jun 2020
Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam11 contributions2 helpful votes
My go to place to stay in Da Nang
Clean spacious rooms, Very nice indoor pool and outstanding staff make this my first choice when I look for Hotel in Da Nang. I work here once a month and have been staying here since it opened. Aunty Thu the cook always has a smile on her face and makes great breakfast. Thai and other front desk staff make the stay very enjoyable. It is a very easy quick walk to the beach and many restaurants close by also. Little Vin Mart is close now also.
Date of stay: June 2020
